author: Liara I'Sorry
text: What I'm seeing in this trailer doesn't work.  1. The story is too generic. 2. No romance/comedy = straight Action/Adventure.  Very hard sell and just not fun to watch. Imagine Princess Bride without the romance or comedy.  Eek.  I see silly behavior which does not equate with funny. Leads to point 3. Characters here are too cartoony and silly, if they can't take this movie and it's premise seriously (universe under threat) why should I? The X-men had moments of levity but they weren't cartoonish and making a mockery of the very film/world their in.  4. The main villain is weak.  A hero is only as good as his/her villain. You're not going to see James Bond matched up against a 12 year old paper boy.  That would be a short and silly fight.  I hear the main villain talking big but I'm not believing it. She's just way too pretty/perfect to take seriously.  Perfect people aren't angry/threatening, they are boring.

I do like Kamala and her family though, but not sure it will get me into the theatre.  Captain Marvel suffers from the "Superman problem" in that there's just not much as stake.  I'll wait to see what friends think of it.  We'll see

text:
There is NO 'unnecessary' hate for this. Disney has released simply AWFUL products for several years now and blamed everyone but themselves in horrible ways. They are awful people and deserve the failure they're experiencing now and will continue to experience. 

You, MCU/Brie lover who wants to dismiss me as a hater: watch the total box office for this be under 400m total and know that means it LOST ABOUT 150 MILLION DOLLARS for Disney (220m budget after their tax rebate, 110m marketing, 50% box office take = 660m break even points. Well below 400m Box office means below 200m earned on a 330m spend. 

Dismiss me if you want and stick your fingers in your ears but enjoy this because Disney are DONE they can't keep losing money like this and the reason it has died is simple: a mix of TERRIBLE writing and DISGUSTING hatred spewed from disney to explain why their films flop - it's our fault not theirs. 

I personally feel sorry for Brie and the rest of the cast being made into hated people as puppets in Disney's excuse marketing machine. I don't think she deserves the hate because I think she was told to say and do everything by them.  She's a scapegoat. The real villains are the upper end of Disney and FINALLY they're paying the price and this is just the beginning (check their stock price if you don't believe me). Bye bye MCU, loved you phase 1-3, you ran 2008-2025/2026 then ended just WATCH

author: Thorne Worthington
text:
Last night in my facebook feed there were about five messages from Marvel, screeching ugly insults about "sexistt incels" who cannot handle a "powerful woman."

This is what Hollywood considers to be effective marketing nowadays:  spitting poison at the public.

It's like radical Leftist politics have actually rotted their brain.   They have taken Leftist identity politics and made it into literally a cult religion.  

RADICAL LEFTISM NOW HAS ALL THE USUAL QUALITIES ASSOCIATED WITH CULT BEHAVIOR.

author: Jordan Verbeek
text:
I won't deny Guardians gave us the best and worst changes of the MCU.
Firstly, they introduced the cosmic side of the universe. Thor and Dr. Strange have both shown the good, bad and ugly side of this.
Secondly, goofy humour perpetrated the MCU and made it hard to bridge the gap between humourous scenes and dramatic scenes (see the airport scene from Civil War to see what I mean).

I'm interested to see the Marvels, but it'll only work if they balance out the two points I've found difficult with the MCU. It will be hard to convince me that the film will be a game changer, but it doesn't hurt if the Marvels turns out to be a great popcorn film like Thor: Ragnarok.

author: raremage
text:
I want to like this. I mean I love Marvel comics and Endgame was my childhood writ large on the big screen, it literally brought tears to my eyes.

But this feels so much like Marvel trying to force two characters who really haven‚Äôt had much comic success down my throat.  I mean, Ms Marvel has been rebooted again and again and again in the comics and just hasn‚Äôt cracked the fandom.  Captain Marvel is amazing but adding in Monica Rambeau is, again, a character of very limited success in the comic world, it just doesn‚Äôt excite me the way I wish it did.

Just about every movie leading up to Infinity War and then Endgame was better than the one before it.  Now it feels like they‚Äôre cranking out movies to keep things busy while all the fans are waiting hungrily for the X-Men and Fantastic Four to start rolling.  

I‚Äôd love to be wrong but I bet I‚Äôm not.
